.START 

P&S 

To earn its poetic license, 

It's been known to indulge in punning, 

And, even worse, when pertaining to verse, 

It sometimes leaves its meter running. 

In this fast-moving world where the daily news 

Gives them much reason to find fault, 

We hope readers continue to take it all 

With a grain of Pepper -- and Salt] 

-- George O. Ludcke. 

Parenthood 

Of all the facts that they could withhold, 

One causes me most ire: 

When I took this job they never told 

Me I could not retire. 

-- Mary Mobilia. 

Daffynition 

Street psychiatrist: insight trader. 

-- Bert Murray. 

